definitions.definition: Which , especially which of an open-ended set of possibilities.
examples: What colour are you going to use?
What kind of car is that?
Did you buy the groceries? — With what money? We barely have any left.
I wonder what colour he is going to use.
I know what colour I am going to use.
That depends on what answer is received.
He seems to have lost what sense he had.
What money I earn is soon spent.

definitions.definition: Emphasises that something is noteworthy or remarkable in quality or degree, in either a good or bad way; may be used in combination with certain other determiners, especially 'a', less often 'some'.

subdefinitions.definition: Used to form exclamations indicating that something is remarkable, in either a good or bad way.

main_definition: ( interrogative ) Which , especially which of an open-ended set of possibilities.
secondary_definitions: ( relative ) Any ... that; all ... that; whatever .
Emphasises that something is noteworthy or remarkable in quality or degree, in either a good or bad way; may be used in combination with certain other determiners, especially 'a', less often 'some'.
